            <para>Since the ESC has electronically programmable inputs and outputs, ESC configuration will vary from
                vehicle to vehicle.
            </para>
            <para>The ESC is mounted in the right side dash panel on the inside of the cab. It is powered from the
                batteries in the engine compartment through the 175 Amp Megafuse, body builder feed stud and a 125 Amp
                Megafuse.
            </para>
            <para>Power for components controlled by switches and the switch packs is supplied from the ESC.</para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>The ESC is not a repairable module. Once it has been determined that the ESC has an internal
                        malfunction, it must be replaced and the replacement must be programmed. There is a chance that
                        reloading the programming might repair some problems.
                    </para>
                </note>
                <note>
                    <para>If the ESC is to be replaced, REPLACE WITH ONLY IC CORPORATION BE/CE BUS ESC MODULES. Any
                        other International Truck or IC Corporation ESC modules are NOT compatible with the IC
                        Corporation BE/CE Bus.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
